{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"There's something about caves --"},{"time":4560,"text":"a shadowy opening in a limestone\ncliff that draws you in."},{"time":9800,"text":"As you pass through the portal\nbetween light and dark,"},{"time":13480,"text":"you enter a subterranean world --"},{"time":16040,"text":"a place of perpetual gloom,\nof earthy smells, of hushed silence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":22800,"text":"Long ago in Europe,"},{"time":24160,"text":"ancient people also entered\nthese underground worlds."},{"time":27640,"text":"As witness to their passage,"},{"time":29080,"text":"they left behind mysterious\nengravings and paintings,"},{"time":32759,"text":"like this panel of humans, triangles\nand zigzags from Ojo Guare√±a in Spain."},{"time":40000,"text":"You now walk the same path\nas these early artists."},{"time":43800,"text":"And in this surreal, otherworldly place,"},{"time":46840,"text":"it's almost possible to imagine"},{"time":48760,"text":"that you hear the muffled footfall\nof skin boots on soft earth,"},{"time":53320,"text":"or that you see the flickering of a torch\naround the next bend."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57600,"text":"When I'm in a cave,"},{"time":59000,"text":"I often find myself wondering\nwhat drove these people to go so deep"},{"time":65120,"text":"to brave dangerous and narrow\npassageways to leave their mark?"},{"time":68840,"text":"In this video clip,"},{"time":70080,"text":"that was shot half a kilometer,\nor about a third of a mile, underground,"},{"time":73480,"text":"in the cave of Cudon in Spain,"},{"time":75640,"text":"we found a series\nof red paintings on a ceiling"},{"time":78120,"text":"in a previously unexplored\nsection of the cave."},{"time":81080,"text":"As we crawled forward, military-style,\nwith the ceiling getting ever lower,"},{"time":85760,"text":"we finally got to a point\nwhere the ceiling was so low"},{"time":89000,"text":"that my husband\nand project photographer, Dylan,"},{"time":91280,"text":"could no longer achieve focus\non the ceiling with his DSLR camera."},{"time":95440,"text":"So while he filmed me,"},{"time":97120,"text":"I kept following the trail of red paint\nwith a single light"},{"time":100440,"text":"and a point-and-shoot camera\nthat we kept for that type of occasion."},{"time":105680,"text":"Half a kilometer underground."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108480,"text":"Seriously."},{"time":109840,"text":"What was somebody doing down there\nwith a torch or a stone lamp?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":112864,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":114080,"text":"I mean -- me, it makes sense, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":116000,"text":"But you know,"},{"time":117240,"text":"this is the kind of question that\nI'm trying to answer with my research."},{"time":121080,"text":"I study some of the oldest\nart in the world."},{"time":124560,"text":"It was created by these\nearly artists in Europe,"},{"time":126880,"text":"between 10,000 and 40,000 years ago."},{"time":131480,"text":"And the thing is"},{"time":132720,"text":"that I'm not just studying it\nbecause it's beautiful,"},{"time":135240,"text":"though some of it certainly is."},{"time":137520,"text":"But what I'm interested in\nis the development of the modern mind,"},{"time":141520,"text":"of the evolution of creativity,\nof imagination, of abstract thought,"},{"time":146480,"text":"about what it means to be human."},{"time":151120,"text":"While all species communicate\nin one way or another,"},{"time":154320,"text":"only we humans have really\ntaken it to another level."},{"time":157920,"text":"Our desire and ability\nto share and collaborate"},{"time":160520,"text":"has been a huge part of our success story."},{"time":163200,"text":"Our modern world is based on a global\nnetwork of information exchange"},{"time":168040,"text":"made possible, in large part,\nby our ability to communicate --"},{"time":172080,"text":"in particular, using graphic\nor written forms of communication."},{"time":176520,"text":"The thing is, though,"},{"time":177800,"text":"that we've been building\non the mental achievements"},{"time":180360,"text":"of those that came before us for so long"},{"time":183440,"text":"that it's easy to forget that certain\nabilities haven't already existed."},{"time":188760,"text":"It's one of the things\nI find most fascinating"},{"time":191160,"text":"about studying our deep history."},{"time":193760,"text":"Those people didn't have the shoulders\nof any giants to stand on."},{"time":197880,"text":"They were the original shoulders."},{"time":200360,"text":"And while a surprising number\nof important inventions"},{"time":203280,"text":"come out of that distant time,"},{"time":205200,"text":"what I want to talk to you about today\nis the invention of graphic communication."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210680,"text":"There are three\nmain types of communication,"},{"time":212880,"text":"spoken, gestural --\nso things like sign language --"},{"time":216280,"text":"and graphic communication."},{"time":218600,"text":"Spoken and gestural are\nby their very nature ephemeral."},{"time":222280,"text":"It requires close contact\nfor a message to be sent and received."},{"time":226240,"text":"And after the moment\nof transmission, it's gone forever."},{"time":230200,"text":"Graphic communication, on the other hand,\ndecouples that relationship."},{"time":234200,"text":"And with its invention,\nit became possible for the first time"},{"time":238200,"text":"for a message to be\ntransmitted and preserved"},{"time":241080,"text":"beyond a single moment in place and time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244800,"text":"Europe is one of the first places"},{"time":246600,"text":"that we start to see graphic marks\nregularly appearing"},{"time":249320,"text":"in caves, rock shelters\nand even a few surviving open-air sites."},{"time":254240,"text":"But this is not the Europe we know today."},{"time":256800,"text":"This was a world dominated\nby towering ice sheets,"},{"time":259800,"text":"three to four kilometers high,"},{"time":261800,"text":"with sweeping grass plains\nand frozen tundra."},{"time":265080,"text":"This was the Ice Age."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268080,"text":"Over the last century,"},{"time":269400,"text":"more than 350 Ice Age rock art sites\nhave been found across the continent,"},{"time":274720,"text":"decorated with animals, abstract shapes\nand even the occasional human"},{"time":279120,"text":"like these engraved figures\nfrom Grotta dell'Addaura in Sicily."},{"time":282760,"text":"They provide us with a rare glimpse"},{"time":284840,"text":"into the creative world and imagination\nof these early artists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":289840,"text":"Since their discovery,"},{"time":291240,"text":"it's been the animals that have received\nthe majority of the study"},{"time":295200,"text":"like this black horse\nfrom Cullalvera in Spain,"},{"time":298400,"text":"or this unusual purple bison\nfrom La Pasiega."},{"time":302880,"text":"But for me, it was the abstract shapes,\nwhat we call geometric signs,"},{"time":308280,"text":"that drew me to study the art."},{"time":311240,"text":"The funny this is that at most sites"},{"time":313560,"text":"the geometric signs far outnumber\nthe animal and human images."},{"time":318080,"text":"But when I started on this back in 2007,"},{"time":321280,"text":"there wasn't even a definitive list\nof how many shapes there were,"},{"time":325280,"text":"nor was there a strong sense"},{"time":326640,"text":"of whether the same ones\nappeared across space or time."},{"time":332120,"text":"Before I could even\nget started on my questions,"},{"time":335240,"text":"my first step was to compile a database"},{"time":337360,"text":"of all known geometric signs\nfrom all of the rock art sites."},{"time":341280,"text":"The problem was that while they were\nwell documented at some sites,"},{"time":344880,"text":"usually the ones\nwith the very nice animals,"},{"time":347200,"text":"there was also a large number of them\nwhere it was very vague --"},{"time":350880,"text":"there wasn't a lot\nof description or detail."},{"time":353160,"text":"Some of them hadn't been visited\nin half a century or more."},{"time":356520,"text":"These were the ones\nthat I targeted for my field work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":359960,"text":"Over the course of two years,"},{"time":361840,"text":"my faithful husband Dylan and I\neach spent over 300 hours underground,"},{"time":367080,"text":"hiking, crawling and wriggling\naround 52 sites"},{"time":371080,"text":"in France, Spain, Portugal and Sicily."},{"time":374040,"text":"And it was totally worth it."},{"time":375920,"text":"We found new, undocumented geometric signs\nat 75 percent of the sites we visited."},{"time":382680,"text":"This is the level of accuracy\nI knew I was going to need"},{"time":385520,"text":"if I wanted to start answering\nthose larger questions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388720,"text":"So let's get to those answers."},{"time":391320,"text":"Barring a handful of outliers,\nthere are only 32 geometric signs."},{"time":395960,"text":"Only 32 signs"},{"time":397800,"text":"across a 30,000-year time span\nand the entire continent of Europe."},{"time":403720,"text":"That is a very small number."},{"time":406320,"text":"Now, if these were random\ndoodles or decorations,"},{"time":408800,"text":"we would expect to see\na lot more variation,"},{"time":411240,"text":"but instead what we find\nare the same signs"},{"time":413680,"text":"repeating across both space and time."},{"time":416920,"text":"Some signs start out strong,\nbefore losing popularity and vanishing,"},{"time":420840,"text":"while other signs are later inventions."},{"time":423200,"text":"But 65 percent of those signs stayed\nin use during that entire time period --"},{"time":428840,"text":"things like lines, rectangles\ntriangles, ovals and circles"},{"time":433160,"text":"like we see here\nfrom the end of the Ice Age,"},{"time":435327,"text":"at a 10,000-year-old site\nhigh in the Pyrenees Mountains."},{"time":439280,"text":"And while certain signs\nspan thousands of kilometers,"},{"time":442520,"text":"other signs had much more\nrestricted distribution patterns,"},{"time":445520,"text":"with some being limited\nto a single territory,"},{"time":447960,"text":"like we see here\nwith these divided rectangles"},{"time":450160,"text":"that are only found in northern Spain,"},{"time":452400,"text":"and which some researchers have speculated"},{"time":454480,"text":"could be some sort\nof family or clan signs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":457880,"text":"On a side note,"},{"time":459280,"text":"there is surprising degree\nof similarity in the earliest rock art"},{"time":462720,"text":"found all the way from France and Spain\nto Indonesia and Australia."},{"time":467320,"text":"With many of the same signs\nappearing in such far-flung places,"},{"time":471640,"text":"especially in that 30,000\nto 40,000-year range,"},{"time":474640,"text":"it's starting to seem increasingly likely"},{"time":477520,"text":"that this invention actually traces back\nto a common point of origin in Africa."},{"time":482400,"text":"But that I'm afraid,\nis a subject for a future talk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":485040,"text":"So back to the matter at hand."},{"time":486880,"text":"There could be no doubt that these signs\nwere meaningful to their creators,"},{"time":490880,"text":"like these 25,000-year-old\nbas-relief sculptures"},{"time":493720,"text":"from La Roque de Venasque in France."},{"time":496360,"text":"We might not know what they meant,\nbut the people of the time certainly did."},{"time":501760,"text":"The repetition of the same signs,\nfor so long, and at so many sites"},{"time":507840,"text":"tells us that the artists\nwere making intentional choices."},{"time":511800,"text":"If we're talking about geometric shapes,"},{"time":514200,"text":"with specific, culturally recognized,\nagreed-upon meanings,"},{"time":518960,"text":"than we could very well be looking"},{"time":520640,"text":"at one of the oldest systems\nof graphic communication in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525200,"text":"I'm not talking about writing yet."},{"time":527120,"text":"There's just not enough\ncharacters at this point"},{"time":529480,"text":"to have represented all of the words\nin the spoken language,"},{"time":532360,"text":"something which is a requirement\nfor a full writing system."},{"time":535200,"text":"Nor do we see the signs\nrepeating regularly enough"},{"time":537600,"text":"to suggest that they were\nsome sort of alphabet."},{"time":540280,"text":"But what we do have\nare some intriguing one-offs,"},{"time":543120,"text":"like this panel from La Pasiega in Spain,\nknown as \"The Inscription,\""},{"time":547720,"text":"with its symmetrical markings on the left,"},{"time":550280,"text":"possible stylized representations\nof hands in the middle,"},{"time":553520,"text":"and what looks a bit\nlike a bracket on the right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":557080,"text":"The oldest systems of graphic\ncommunication in the world --"},{"time":559960,"text":"Sumerian cuneiform, Egyptian hieroglyphs,\nthe earliest Chinese script,"},{"time":564920,"text":"all emerged between 4,000\nand 5,000 years ago,"},{"time":568520,"text":"with each coming into existence\nfrom an earlier protosystem"},{"time":571680,"text":"made up of counting marks\nand pictographic representations,"},{"time":575240,"text":"where the meaning\nand the image were the same."},{"time":577640,"text":"So a picture of a bird would really\nhave represented that animal."},{"time":581880,"text":"It's only later that we start to see\nthese pictographs become more stylized,"},{"time":586640,"text":"until they almost become unrecognizable"},{"time":589000,"text":"and that we also start to see\nmore symbols being invented"},{"time":592040,"text":"to represent all those other\nmissing words in language --"},{"time":594960,"text":"things like pronouns, adverbs, adjectives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598160,"text":"So knowing all this,"},{"time":599720,"text":"it seems highly unlikely that\nthe geometric signs from Ice Age Europe"},{"time":603600,"text":"were truly abstract written characters."},{"time":606320,"text":"Instead, what's much more likely"},{"time":608560,"text":"is that these early artists\nwere also making counting marks,"},{"time":612560,"text":"maybe like this row of lines\nfrom Riparo di Za Minic in Sicily,"},{"time":616600,"text":"as well as creating\nstylized representations"},{"time":619240,"text":"of things from the world around them."},{"time":621760,"text":"Could some of the signs\nbe weaponry or housing?"},{"time":624400,"text":"Or what about celestial objects\nlike star constellations?"},{"time":628560,"text":"Or maybe even rivers, mountains,\ntrees -- landscape features,"},{"time":633200,"text":"possibly like this black penniform\nsurrounded by strange bell-shaped signs"},{"time":637600,"text":"from the site of El Castillo in Spain."},{"time":640200,"text":"The term penniform\nmeans \"feather-shaped\" in Latin,"},{"time":643520,"text":"but could this actually be\na depiction of a plant or a tree?"},{"time":647720,"text":"Some researchers have begun\nto ask these questions"},{"time":650720,"text":"about certain signs at specific sites,"},{"time":653640,"text":"but I believe the time has come\nto revisit this category as a whole."},{"time":658560,"text":"The irony in all of this, of course,"},{"time":660320,"text":"is that having just carefully classified\nall of the signs into a single category,"},{"time":664640,"text":"I have a feeling that my next step\nwill involve breaking it back apart"},{"time":668160,"text":"as different types of imagery\nare identified and separated off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":672440,"text":"Now don't get me wrong,"},{"time":673680,"text":"the later creation\nof fully developed writing"},{"time":676320,"text":"was an impressive feat in its own right."},{"time":678960,"text":"But it's important to remember"},{"time":680440,"text":"that those early writing systems\ndidn't come out of a vacuum."},{"time":683760,"text":"And that even 5,000 years ago,"},{"time":685760,"text":"people were already building\non something much older,"},{"time":689120,"text":"with its origins stretching back\ntens of thousands of years --"},{"time":692880,"text":"to the geometric signs\nof Ice Age Europe and far beyond,"},{"time":697000,"text":"to that point, deep\nin our collective history,"},{"time":700320,"text":"when someone first came up with the idea\nof making a graphic mark,"},{"time":704400,"text":"and forever changed the nature\nof how we communicate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707360,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":708600,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}